{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17537041","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17537041"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T17:13:23+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T17:13:23+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15901"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15901","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15901"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.12,0.42,0.1,0.24,0.12]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8592"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63067"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8592","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8592"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15901"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48518"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"37"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"3496"},{"type":"tags","id":"4648"},{"type":"tags","id":"4649"},{"type":"tags","id":"4790"},{"type":"tags","id":"4955"},{"type":"tags","id":"4966"},{"type":"tags","id":"4983"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11629"},{"type":"tags","id":"11643"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20594"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36981"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63067","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/63067"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 24-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a three-week history of intense itching in his pubic region. He reports having unprotected sexual intercourse with a new partner six weeks ago. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. On examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Examination of the pubic region reveals excoriations from scratching and small bluish brown macules on the skin underlying the pubic hair. Using magnification, small grey-brown organisms are visible attached to the hair shafts, along with small white oval structures firmly adherent to the hair.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate first-line treatment?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Oral ivermectin","Pyrethrins with piperonyl butoxide foam","Malathion lotion","Shaving of pubic hair","Benzyl benzoate lotion"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with classic features of pubic lice (\u003Cem\u003EPhthirus pubis\u003C/em\u003E) infestation. The diagnosis is confirmed by the presence of bluish brown macules (maculae cerulae) and visible organisms and eggs attached to pubic hair shafts.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPyrethrins with piperonyl butoxide foam\u003C/strong\u003E is the first-line treatment for pubic lice. It should be applied to all hairy areas of the body below the neck (though can be used on the head if also affected) and washed off after 10 minutes. A second application after 7 days is recommended to ensure complete eradication. It is effective in killing both lice and eggs.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOral ivermectin\u003C/strong\u003E is not a first-line treatment for pubic lice. While it can be effective, it is typically reserved for cases that have failed topical therapy or where topical treatment is impractical.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMalathion lotion\u003C/strong\u003E is an alternative pediculicide but is not first-line treatment. It requires a longer application time of 8-12 hours before being washed off, which may be impractical for some people given it\u0027s strong odour.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile it may remove some lice and nits, \u003Cstrong\u003Eshaving of pubic hair\u003C/strong\u003E is not recommended. It does not ensure complete eradication, and given the effective and easy option of topical treatments, it is an unnecessary step.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBenzyl benzoate lotion\u003C/strong\u003E is an alternative treatment for pubic lice but is not first-line due to skin irritation and the availability of more effective options. Additionally, it needs to be left on the skin for 24 hours prior to being washed off, which can be difficult for patients.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn addition to chemical treatment, the patient should ensure that all bedding and clothing should be washed in hot water (at least 60\u00b0C) to prevent reinfestation. There are no strict guidelines about contact tracing, though it is recommended that all sexual contacts from the previous four to six weeks should be treated simultaneously, as well as any close household contacts.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Pyrethrins with piperonyl butoxide foam is the first-line treatment for pubic lice infestation as it is easy to apply and can be washed off after 10 minutes","Sexual partners should be treated concurrently to prevent reinfestation","A second application of treatment after 7 days is recommended to ensure complete eradication"],"references":["Patel PU, Tan A, Levell NJ. A clinical review and history of pubic lice. Clin Exp Dermatol. 2021 Oct;46(7):1181-1188. doi: 10.1111/ced.14666. Epub 2021 May 12. Erratum in: Clin Exp Dermatol. 2021 Dec;46(8):1665. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33811771/","Ectoparasites - STI Guidelines Australia [Internet]. 2021. Available at: https://sti.guidelines.org.au/sexually-transmissible-infections/ectoparasites/","Pubic lice treatment guidelines - Melbourne Sexual Health Centre (MSHC). www.mshc.org.au. Available at: https://www.mshc.org.au/health-professionals/treatment-guidelines/pubic-lice-treatment-guidelines"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48518"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15901"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48518","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/48518"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-19T22:03:42+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-19T22:03:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8592"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"63067"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"3","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/3"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddf4","name":"Dermatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"37","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/37"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf46","name":"Sexual Health","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":nu